{
  "texts": [
    "Importance of specific molecular substructuresTo investigate which parts of the molecule played an important role in predicting DILI, several compounds in the test data were analyzed.",
    "Among the true positive compounds, the compounds with high prediction probabilities (p ≥ 0.8) were Pazopanib, Rifampin, Itraconazole, Imatinib, Dactinomycin, Tasosartan, and Atorvastatin.",
    "The molecular substructures that significantly contributed to the DILI were highlighted through their attention weights.",
    "The three most important molecular substructures with high attention weights in each compound are displayed in Additional file 1: Fig.",
    "Several highlighted results of the analysis were further compared with external literature.Aniline derivatives commonly in Pazopanib and Dactinomycin influenced the prediction of DILI (Fig. 6a, c)."
  ]
}